Sonal Vaid

Content Curator | Updated On - Apr 12, 2022

GATE Question Paperincludes 65 multiple-choice questions (MCQs), multiple select questions (MSQs) and Numerical Answer Type (NATs).As per GATE Exam Pattern, 15% weightage of marks is given to General Aptitude section, 13% to Engineering Mathematics, and the remaining 72% to the core subject paper.However, for disciplines like the AR, CY, EY, GG, MA, PH, and XL, there are only two sections in the question paperi.e. General Aptitude section carrying 15% of the total marks and the remaining for the specific discipline.

Frequently Asked Questions

GATE Question Paper FAQs

Ques.Where can I download GATE question papers?

Ans. GATE Question Paper PDFs can be downloaded from the official website after the conclusion of the exam. However, direct link to download GATE Previous year Question Paper PDFs with Answer Key is available on our page here. Candidates can use the tables and the links below to download year-wise GATE Question Papers for 2022, 2021, 2020, 2019, 2018, 2017, 2016, 2015, 2014, 2013, 2012 and 2011.

Ques. Will I also find solutions to GATE Question Papers in the official PDFs?

Ans. The official GATE Question Papers released by the exam conducting authorities are accompanied with the official answer keys. Therefore candidates can check the correct answer to each of the questions asked. Candidates looking for solutions to GATE Question Papers can check NTPEL (National Programme on Technology Enhanced Learning) aneducational initiative, involving 7 IITs (Bombay, Delhi, Guwahati, Kanpur, Kharagpur, Madras, Roorkee) and IISc Bangalore. NTPEL provides video solutions to some of the popularGATE papers such as Computer Science, Mechanical Engineering, Civil Engineering, etc. Check GATE NPTEL Official Website

Ques.Which paper is tough in GATE?

Ans. Although each paper in GATE exam is considered to be tough due to the high competition. In 2021, about 7.1 lakh candidates appeared for GATE 2021, of which only17.82% qualified the exam. However, considering the paper analysis released for GATE 2022, the Mechanical Engineering paper was reported to be tough in terms of overall difficulty. Check Detailed GATE 2022 Paper Analysis

Ques. How many questions are there in GATE Question Paper?

Ans. GATE Question Paper consists of 65 questions in total. 10 questions are from the General Aptitude section (common section in all 29 papers) while the rest 55 questions are from Core Discipline. GATE exam consists of 1 mark and 2 marks questions. Check GATE Exam Pattern and Marking Scheme

Ques. I am studying in the final year of Computer Science Engineering, will there be any questions from the syllabus of the final year as well in GATE CSE Question Paper?

Ans. Yes, GATE Question Paper isdesigned to testthe candidates knowledge on all the subjects that are studied during their Engineering degree including that of the fourth and final year as well. Thus, candidates are always advised to study the content of the final year in advance to be able to sit and be successful in their attempt at GATE exam.

Ques.Is there any significant change in the exam pattern of GATE? I am planning to test my knowledge based on GATE Previous Year Question Papers.

Ans. No changes had been made in GATE 2022 Exam Pattern for all the subjects except Architecture and Planning (AR).The paper now consists of two sections- General Aptitude (for 15 marks) and Core Subject further divided into Part A (for 60 marks mandatory for everyone) and Part B (for 25 marks with two optional sections-Part B1 (Architecture) and Part B2 (Planning)). Candidates have to choose one of the two parts from Part Bduring the exam. Additionally, two new subjects were added in GATE 2022- Naval Architecture & Marine Engineering (NM) and Geomatics Engineering (GE).

Ques. Are candidates allowed to use a physical calculator to solve long and complex calculations asked in GATE Question Paper?

Ans.No. All the candidates are provided with an online virtual scientific calculator to be used to answer the questions. Nophysical calculator is allowed inside the exam hall. Candidates can attempt various GATE Mock Tests to get a hand on the virtual calculator provided in GATE exam.Check GATE Virtual Calculator

Ques.What are the benefits of solving GATE PreviousYearQuestion Papers?

Ans.Solving GATE previous year Question Papers helps a candidate in better exam preparation. Mentioned below are some of the other benefits of solving GATE Question Papers-

  • Understanding the exam pattern and find little changes in the exam pattern that are made to trick the candidate. For example, for 2021, papers such as CSE, IN, CE, etc. had very few MSQs as compared to the previous year trends.
  • Solving various GATE sample papers and previous year papers might help candidates find topics/ concepts that havent been covered in the syllabus as such. Thus, it helps in assessing the overall exam preparation level.
  • Solving various sample papers and previous year GATE Question Paper helps candidates in boosting their confidence along with working on the speed and accuracy.
  • Also solving GATE Question Papers available in the form of official mock tests on the official website helps candidates get acquainted with the actual paper and the screen that will be displayed on the exam day.

*The article might have information for the previous academic years, which will be updated soon subject to the notification issued by the University/College.
